articles.title: JetBlue cuts more unprofitable routes, tweaks Europe flights - CNBC
articles.description: JetBlue is in the middle of a new plan to return to consistent profitability and cut costs.
articles.content: JetBlue Airways told staff Wednesday that it is axing more unprofitable flights, redeploying aircraft outfitted with its high-value business class and tweaking Europe service, the carrier's latest mo… [+2053 chars]
